      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Mercy-USA demonstrates a strong commitment to infrastructure-led development. By providing <cite id=\"13\">water berkads for 10,000 beneficiaries</cite>, they address the root causes of waterborne illness rather than just treating symptoms. Their financial health is bolstered by <cite id=\"14\">100% independent board members</cite>, ensuring objective oversight of their <cite id=\"3\">$54 million budget</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "Mercy-USA for Aid and Development is a humanitarian institution that has provided life-saving relief and sustainable development since its <cite id=\"1\">founding in 1988</cite>. The organization specializes in nutrition, health services, and clean water infrastructure, with a primary focus on vulnerable populations in <cite id=\"2\">Somalia, Syria, and Gaza</cite>. In 2023, the charity reported <cite id=\"3\">$54,067,823 in total revenue</cite>, maintaining a large-scale operation that reaches across <cite id=\"4\">Kenya, Albania, Yemen, and Bosnia</cite>. Their work is characterized by a high degree of specialization in medical outcomes, such as maintaining an <cite id=\"5\">80% tuberculosis cure rate</cite> in their Somalia health centers. Beyond emergency aid, Mercy-USA invests in long-term stability through infrastructure, having <cite id=\"6\">built 950 modular homes</cite> for displaced families and <cite id=\"7\">repaired 800 water wells</cite> to ensure community health. The organization operates with high financial efficiency, spending only <cite id=\"8\">$0.02 to raise every $1</cite> in donations. This lean fundraising model allows the charity to maximize the resources sent to the field. While the organization is a major player in the international humanitarian space, it maintains <cite id=\"9\">strong ties to the US Muslim community</cite> through domestic grantmaking and zakat-eligible programming.",
